<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1866-01-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1866-01-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="383" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d383">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Burlingame</persName></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 159.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1866-01-29"><hi rend="italic">January</hi> 29, 1866.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I enclose for your information A copy of
                            Mr. Adams’s despatch,<note n="*" xml:id="d383fn1">For enclosure see
                                correspondence with Great Britain.</note> No. 1126, of the 4th of
                            January, and its accompaniments, relative to the disposition of the
                            Osborne flotilla, it being a reply to my instructions to him upon that
                            subject, in compliance with your suggestion.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Anson Burlingame</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>